<section class="block-section story">
  <span class="section-tag">Story</span>
  <h2>Why this block matters</h2>
  <p class="sub">The highest-leverage teacher move of the unit. Watch the reasoning live, then apply it.</p>
  <p>Today Mr. Ignash demonstrates a complete Landscape Reading on a familiar location — likely the <strong>AISC campus drainage system</strong> or a segment of <strong>Marina Beach</strong>. The point is to make the reasoning move visible: <em>here's the evidence I'm looking at; here's the inference I'm drawing; here's the inference I'm declining to draw because the evidence won't support it</em>. The Pallikaranai Marsh worked-example doc is the exemplar (printed + in Classroom; a site version is coming) — you'll see something similar built in front of you.</p>
  <p>Then OPVL practice. Most of your Landscape Reading sources will be government data (GSI, Bhuvan, IMD) and news. The OPVL moves on those sources are different from the news/textbook OPVL of Unit 0. Geological data has its own kind of Limitation — accuracy depends on when the survey was done, what method was used, what spatial resolution. Today's the day to internalize that.</p>
</section>

