<section class="block-section do">
  <span class="section-tag">Do</span>
  <h2>Today's work — choose one path</h2>
  <p class="sub">All four paths end the same: at least one completed OPVL on a source for your chosen location. The path you pick is about how deep you go.</p>
  <div class="choice-intro">
    <strong>Learning Intention:</strong> {{ learningIntention | safe }}
  </div>
  <div class="choice-board">
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">A</div>
      <div class="choice-title">OPVL on your primary source (default)</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">Pick your strongest source for your Landscape Reading location and complete full OPVL on it. Focus on Limitation — make it specific (date of survey, spatial resolution, contested interpretation, etc.), not generic.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Solo · Default</span>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">B</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Contested news source</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">Find one news source that makes a contested claim about your location (e.g., "the Cooum is irrecoverable" or "Marina Beach is the world's longest"). Apply OPVL. Stretch: cross-check the claim against the GSI or government data and document the disagreement.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Solo · Stretch</span>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">C</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Continue drafting</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">If your OPVL is already solid, spend the block extending your landscape biography. The worked example just demoed should be fresh — apply the same move-by-move logic to your own location.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Solo · Choice</span>
    </div>
